        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} ten days, where we're spending our annual "wind-down vacation" this time. The airport was extremely crowded, but since we had already checked in, we could drop off our suitcases at the self-service bag drop and go straight to security. Fortunately, we didn't have to wait long and could make ourselves comfortable in the upper part of the airport. </p>
        <p> After a mini breakfast - it was just too early - we went to the gate. Luckily, we got seats with more legroom and made ourselves more or less comfortable in row 8 after boarding. With almost 20 minutes delay, we took off and landed in Tenerife South shortly after 11 a.m. local time. After the Corona checks were done, it was time to wait at the baggage carousel - they took their sweet time this time. </p>
        <p> Once we had everything together, we went to the TUI bus. Here too we waited a while, and after about 30 minutes of driving, we finally arrived at the Riu Arecas Hotel. And here too it was: wait - because there was a fire alarm drill, and everything moved very leisurely. We got drinks as compensation. </p>

